    "\", a single forward pass of the parser takes about 10 seconds and requires roughly 40 GB of VRAM on a single A100 GPU.",
    "While the LLM parser produces highly accurate outputs overall, our current rules do not resolve ambiguous count expressions such as \"a few\", \"several\", \"a couple of\", or plurals without explicit numerals (e.g., \"blades\").",
    "Handling these ambiguous counts is beyond the scope of our experiments, but it could be addressed by sampling counts from a small candidate set, for example N = {3, 4}, or by providing targeted few-shot examples to the LLM.Cross-attention normalization Baseline methods, Attend-and-Excite [10], InitNO [2], and TEBOpt [9], utilize the the softmax normalization technique on cross-attention maps.",
    "It operates by applying the softmax function to the cross-attention maps along the token dimension, excluding the SOT token at index 0.",
    "This sharpens the attention, emphasizing foreground objects while suppressing background noise."
